1. Ab hier ursprnglicher Brief von anderer Hand, auf den Hermann Gundert
___obigen Brief schrieb.

                                              Tellicherry 26th. April 1843.
To Reverend Mr. Gunder

Reverend Sir,

.fo +
In reply to your letter I beg to say, that the 2 Cask's of Claret landed
here from Mah‚ not having paid the value of import Certificate, and as one
of them you require to send now to Mangalore, you will be under the neces-
sity to pay half a Rupee the value of stamp Paper and quarter Rupee for
another Re-export stamp Papper. As there is a boat to sail to that station,
I hope you will send the 3/4 Rupee, and avail this oppertunity to send the
above Cask. to Mangalore.
.fo -

                         I remain to be
                           Reverend Sir
                           Your Most Obedient Servant
                           Lt* Fernandes*


